==English==
===Alternative forms===
*dead-pan
*dead pan
===Etymology===
A [[compound word]] formed from the [[English]] [[adjective]] ''[[dead]]'' and [[United States]] slang word ''[[pan]]'' (synonymous to ''"[[face]]"'').

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|ˈdɛdpæn}}
===Adjective===
'''deadpan'''
#
#*Delibeately [[impassive]] or [[expressionless]] [[face]] or [[look]].
#*A person having such a facial expression or look.
#*Used in terms of behaviour, speech, &c. to mean impassive

===Noun===
'''deadpan''' (also '''deadpan comedy''' or '''deadpan humour''')
# A style of [[comedic]] [[delivery]] in which something humourous is said or done while not exhibiting a change in emotion or facial expression.

